{"sectionId":736,"sectionIdLiteral":"736","humanId":"lesson-315","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"All gifts my brothers give belong to me.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 315"},"annotation":"W-315","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-315\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"736#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"736#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Each day a thousand treasures come to me with every passing moment.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"736#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>I am blessed with gifts throughout the day, in value far beyond all things of which I can conceive.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"736#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>A brother smiles upon another, and my heart is gladdened.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"736#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Someone speaks a word of gratitude or mercy, and my mind receives this gift and takes it as its own.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"736#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>And everyone who finds the way to God becomes my savior, pointing out the way to me, and giving me his certainty that what he learned is surely mine as well.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"736#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"736#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>I thank You, Father, for the many gifts that come to me today and every day from every Son of God.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"736#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>My brothers are unlimited in all their gifts to me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"736#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Now may I offer them my thankfulness, that gratitude to them may lead me on to my Creator and His memory.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"Each day a thousand treasures come to me with every passing moment. I am blessed with gifts throughout the day, in value far beyond all things of which I can conceive. A brother smiles upon another,","cont